    <section>
        <h2>What Is a School Management System?</h2>

        <p>
            A School Management System (SMS), also known as a Student Information System (SIS)
            or School ERP, is a centralized software platform that digitizes and automates
            school administration.
        </p>

        <p>
            Rather than using separate tools for attendance, fee collection, examinations,
            scheduling, and communication, schools manage all operations through one integrated system.
        </p>

        <blockquote>
            Software that integrates student records, academics, finances, HR,
            and parent communication into one unified platform, eliminating data silos
            and enabling smarter decision-making.
        </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Why Every School Needs a Management System in 2026</h2>

        <p>
            Digital administration has become the standard across modern education.
            Schools are increasingly adopting management systems to reduce manual work,
            improve transparency, and enhance communication with parents.
        </p>

        <h3>Key Drivers of Adoption</h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Administrative workload reduction</li>
            <li>Improved parent engagement and transparency</li>
            <li>Regulatory compliance and audit readiness</li>
            <li>Automated fee collection and financial reporting</li>
            <li>Multi-campus operational management</li>
            <li>Data-driven decision making</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Core Features of a School Management System</h2>

        <h3>1. Student Information Management</h3>
        <p>
            Centralized student profiles containing admission details,
            academic records, medical information, guardian contacts,
            and important documents.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Attendance Management</h3>
        <p>
            Digital attendance tracking with real-time notifications
            and automated reporting.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Timetable & Scheduling</h3>
        <p>
            Automated timetable generation that prevents scheduling conflicts
            and optimizes resource allocation.
        </p>

        <h3>4. Fee Management & Online Payments</h3>
        <p>
            Complete fee lifecycle management, including invoicing,
            online payments, reminders, and reporting.
        </p>

        <h3>5. Examination & Gradebook Management</h3>
        <p>
            Exam scheduling, grade calculation, report card generation,
            and academic performance tracking.
        </p>

        <h3>6. Parent & Student Portal</h3>
        <p>
            Self-service access to attendance, grades, assignments,
            notices, and communication tools.
        </p>

        <h3>7. HR & Payroll Management</h3>
        <p>
            Employee records, attendance, leave management,
            payroll processing, and performance tracking.
        </p>

        <h3>8. Library Management</h3>
        <p>
            Digital cataloging, issue/return tracking,
            and fine management.
        </p>

        <h3>9. Transport & GPS Tracking</h3>
        <p>
            Route planning, vehicle monitoring,
            and parent notifications.
        </p>

        <h3>10. Analytics & Reporting</h3>
        <p>
            Real-time dashboards for enrollment,
            attendance, academic performance,
            finances, and operational insights.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Types of School Management Systems</h2>

        <h3>Cloud-Based (SaaS)</h3>
        <p>
            Ideal for most schools due to low infrastructure requirements,
            automatic updates, and accessibility from anywhere.
        </p>

        <h3>On-Premise</h3>
        <p>
            Suitable for institutions requiring full data control
            and offline operation.
        </p>

        <h3>Open-Source</h3>
        <p>
            Cost-effective but requires technical expertise
            for deployment and maintenance.
        </p>

        <h3>Mobile-First Platforms</h3>
        <p>
            Designed for schools operating primarily through smartphones
            and tablets.
        </p>

        <h3>Integrated School ERP</h3>
        <p>
            Best suited for school groups and multi-campus institutions.
        </p>
    </section>

